<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <%- include('partials/head'); -%>
    </head>
    <body>
        <%- include('partials/navbar'); -%>

        <main role="main" class="container">
            <div class="encrypto-share">
                <h1>Encrypt Text</h1>
                <div class="form-group row">
                    <input type="text" class="form-control" id="text-to-encrypt" placeholder="Text to encrypt">
                </div>
                <div class="form-group row d-flex justify-content-center" id="submit-button">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" id="encrypt-text">Submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="form-group row d-none justify-content-center" id="share-button">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-clipboard-target="#text-to-encrypt" id="copy-button">Copy to Clipboard</button>
                </div>
                <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid">
                    <div class="container">
                        <p class="lead">Encerypted data is stored on the server and can be accessed only once.<br/>
                        After the encrypted link is visited, the object stored on the server is removed and there is not way to retrive it.</p>
                        <p>The object is decrypted by using generated private and public keys. Public key is part of the URL and not stored on the server.<br/>
                        The private key and the encrypted content are stored on the server.</p>
                        <p>Encryption and decryption processes happen on client browser and not on the server.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <footer class="mastfoot mt-auto">
            <%- include('partials/footer'); -%>
        </footer>
    </body>
</html>